A Healthcare worker prepares to do a swab test on a patient at the Schotsche Kloof Civic Centre in the historical Bo-Kaap district of Cape Town on April 7, 2020. This was the first community-run screening and testing in Bo-kaap. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of death due to COVID-19 in South Africa is now at 48, according to the health ministry. In the latest update, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the country is 2605. “We also note that the number of tests being conducted continues to rise, with the total number of tests conducted to date being 95 060,” the update said. Limpopo and the Eastern Cape have recorded their first deaths. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.